content: Good: Accuracy of rotations. Bad: No female option, no mandible or finger movement, no fart sounds for when you click the pelvis.

For what this app cost you'd think there would be a movable jaw, fingers and toes and a female model for drawing the female frame. As it is now it's really lacking features and feels I've wasted money. No updates since 2019, for a paid app I'd expect these simple things I've mentioned. I'll hold on to it a while longer to see what happens but I'm guessing nothing.
It's nice. But needs a lot more upgradation. To be able to save a newly created pose is one such feature to be added.
Freakin app is awesome.
A must have! Only issue would be there's no screen orientation lock.
i got very frustrated with the controls along with the lack of an undo/redo button.

It would be lovely if the app was as good as your content. The app just doesn't look nice and doesn't work as advertised. If you act on all the customer reviews, this would be a much better app. I'm hoping you update this soon.
Surprisingly easy to pose and I have used many similar software!
Was recommended this app by my professor for my human anatomy for art class in college and it reeeeaally helped with me my assignments quite a lot!
Good app but needs further development its hard to support a stagnant app.
Best customer experience. Great app and its $7 so money really well spent.

App is really helpful for figure drawing, but still it needs some more development in following areas; 1. Rotations of joints should be locked at extreme angles. 2.light transparent removable muscles can be added . 3.some skelly action animations can be the part of this app. 4.zoomed joint rotations with and without muscles can make this app really awesome.
Love this app great for anatomy study

Really nice for pose references when drawing. Easy to use, and I like the simplified skeleton feature as a basic body outline. However, I wish you could change the proportions of the skeleton/bones though, to make it easier to visualize poses on shorter/taller characters and children.
gut!!!
The resolution of the skeleton is quite low.....cannot find a way to save at a higher res....dissapointed.....

Can be improve. Should have button for different side of view (e.g. right & left side view, reset view etc). Too hard to edit when some part is located overlapping. Having side bar to select which part to rotate will better than click on the part.

I love this app, and it's really useful but there is something that I would love seeing and it's that it would be more helpful you muscles were added. So you could like toggle different muscles on and off and also see how they move when you rotate the posable skelly

Not a natural looking model. The range of motion of each body part is utterly unrealistic. Joints rotate 360 degrees and the is no reliable way to determine the actual movement of a person. Plus the model does not take into consideration weight of the body parts. So you cannot change the balance of the figure. Also I found frustrating that it's impossible to tilt the hips to achieve realistic poses. Overall quite a disappointment for the money.

Very awkward unintuitive panting/navigation options. Also, joints can be bent way beyond their natural limit, so in terms of "posing" not so great either. Still a cool app, but nowhere near the top-tier on the market

Thanks for the refund.. these types of apps need manipulation speed adjustment coz its hard to get the hang of it. Proko doesnt seem to care about customer feedback on the app.. we want a muscle system with realistic limits to anatomy manipulation for the poses. Its time consuming to get the pose down when a slight touch makes the limbs fly. 4stars for the refund and skelly needs these improvements then i will gladly buy.
This is 100% less creepy than having a plastic skeleton in my apartment.
The youtube ad of this app shows the skeleton's fingers being posable (fingerguns, peace signs) but in the actual app, they are not.

The biggest flaw is the static hands. It would be beneficial to have at least a closed hand. I'm not sure why so many reviews focus on the price. The price is on point with the smallest cheapest wood mannequin that you'd find in an art supply store. The ribs and the forearms set this app apart from others. Like in the Proko videos, the forearm bones twist like they would in real life, and the ribs stretch to match the position. If you know the anatomy of muscles you won't need anything else.

This app would be so much more useful if you could remove bones you weren't interested in. It is pretty tricky to pose the thing as well. Not sure its worth the money as it stands, might be ok to just save some static images and draw muscles over the top. Considering how good all of Prokos other content is, this is poor really.
i have a question .. please .. can i install this app on PC.. ?
Such an awesome tool.
it's a bit hard to control. Muscles should be included along with some limits to the bones' range of motions
what's up with the rotation? it's super glitchy and I haven't been able to successfully manipulate the dude at all.
exceptional !!

This is awesome for reference, i have some suggestions though. It be great to have the camera rotation pivot to be infront of the camera using the closet body part for the pivot centre( at least for z down the camera view) would make camera setup easier, controls for the field of view on the camera too would be great. Straight up Fk mode is fine, but a quick edit IK mode for the arms and legs would be wonderful. Keep up the excellent work!

If you're looking to simply get the basic pose, this app is great. Unfortunately, apps like this already exist for free and many have detailed mannequins with full skins, a larger library of poses for less money, and props. I love Proko and what they're doing but they need to step it up with this app. Maybe they should include a muscle and skin mode with an expanded pose library....
disappointing. I was expecting an anatomy app - just bones. There are better anatomy apps on Google play for artists

A very simple bare bones reference model. The product feature describing this model as being "fully poseable" is blatantly false. And the lack of finer articulation, labeling of bones, and option to display a transpanrency of a human body over the skeleton is dissapointing. For this price I expected at least articulation for the lower mandible.
Great app, but I wish you could move around the fingers

Not bad, but lacking some features. Would love it if it had: 1.Camera controls, specifically FOV adjustment. 2. Ability to export images. Right now you have to take a screenshot. 3. Pose control sliders like arms up/back, torso & head twist, arm twist, hand grip, etc.
Still too GPU intensive, didn't limit FPS to 1 when no touch input.
fantastic for an artist
Every artist should have this app.
Very nice. Great for reference and drawing study. Looking forward to use it. A portable skeleton!!
Great App but needs to be available on Windows, not very useful on a small Android screen.
Proko es genial, tiene mi apoyo en cada cosa que enseñe, y en cada app que desarrolle para un mejor y más didáctico aprendizaje. Esta App es Muy Buena!

The user interface is very good, the 3D ball gadgets used to manipulate a bones' leaning, tilting and facing are easy to grasp. Robo Skelly is also very nice to have as a simplification for quick sketching.  It it missing a few features though, mainly it's advertised as "fully poseable" but it does not allow opening the lower jaw or bending fingers and toes.  Other features I wish it had would be: -cast shadows and reflected light (as an on/off toggle option) -additional light sources (also as optional toggles) -ability to place arbitrarily sizable and rotatable boxes into the scene along with Skelly (boxes should not cast shadows themselves but only receive cast shadows from Skelly) -more camera control (only allows rotation around two axes at the moment, it's possible to fake rotation around a third one only by posing Skellys pelvis bone instead but that would not be enough as soon as there are additional boxes in the scene) -option to save current view as an image file (can only do that with phones' builtin screenshot feature at the moment)
i wana see skella in this app as well actually!!!
Love Skelly. $7 well spent. It'll be cool if there was actually a real life posable model of Skelly, that'll be cute
I like this app but it can be even better if you can move the fingers.

It's a great tool. Wish for a few more things to be incorporated - 1. 
Wiremesh Display on robo skelly. Not too dense though. Just bare minimum 
lines (It'll help read orientation better) 2. Very basic 3d shapes that can 
be played around with in terms of rotation, scale in perspective. It's such 
a crucial part of learning to draw forms in perspective. It'll be great for 
practice of drawing 100 boxes, cylinders, etc Also if a few 3d shapes can 
be combined by the user. These are things a beginner struggles to visualise 
and draw correctly, yet there is no such app available.

Would give 5 stars if there are any upcoming updates, and cloud syncing for 
saving the poses. Would be better if you can save the models with 
transparent background
soften the glare

amazing, would be 5 stars if you could change Central component from the 
pelvis so that you can rotate pelvis without rotating whole model, really 
frustrating

Awesome to learn the bony guy in an interactive way. Way more interesting 
than just looking at him on papers. Additional, you can also design the 
gesture as you like, change light source, save images, and so on. Perfect 
to support Proko also.

im having a problem trying pose the model, its very laggy and unresponsive 
for me, is there a fix to this?????

This is an amazing app. I love the 'pose library'(options to save and share 
poses), unlimited flexibility (this comes in handy drawing characters and 
understand how bones look in bizarre poses). What would make this an 
invaluable app is if there was features such as; 'MUSCLE LAYER MODE'(so we 
can see how muscles stretch/bulg with the pose) A box/cylinder version of 
Robo Selly (one similar to what we've studied in the course) Options to 
pose HAND/FOOT bones. This is pretty hard to do on its own having this 
option would help with this tedious task. 'Movable Jaw' 'Undo Button' 
'Joint Limitations' (the flexibility is amazing but having an option for 
limitation will help better in understanding the limitations of the average 
human body ). This is a pricey app and as a consumer I do have more 
expectations.

Good app. Really needs the ability to save your own poses. Maybe even share 
poses amongst users.
Thx again for your quality content
Please add muscles on skelly

Love this app! Responsive & invaluable for foreshortening. Two developments I'd love to see: 1. Metacarpal & metatarsal moveability. Would be amazing for action comic artists/animators/sports illustrators. 2. Different indicators for a bone's motion versus its rotation. From side view- Tried to pose an archer - spent five minutes on just the retracting bow arm.  Every click on forearm only rotated the ulna/radius in the same position - could not push elbow behind the torso until I rotated to front view. Don't mind that it wasn't possible, but would've liked to see if a click was activating rotation or positioning. Otherwise - really terrific app! Lighting option is a nice surprise.

Don't think it's still being developed but if it does i really wish they add the muscles/anatomy. The camera movement could use some tweak like pivoting from parts we selected.  Overall the app is good and the features such as lighting, storeable pose, basic form make the app a solid choice for an artist.
Exactly what I was looking for! Can you add a feature to view only skull and only hand please?

The app is excellent as a visual tool. But the absence of joint limitations, which would allow only a realistic range of motion, limits it's usefulness. It is not a simulation of the human skeleton that can be used to generate possible poses. Thus it is no substitute for a "live" model.

I LOVE THIS APP! I immediately fell in love with the amount of control i have with Skelly. My only request is that various skins and muscles (varying proportions, builds, etc) be added for both male and female genders. That would take this app to the NEXT LEVEL (and it would get that 5th star) otherwise, this app is AMAZING. Will definitely recommend this to others. (Also, is a desktop version in the works for Mac/Windows?)

Is there a way to close the skeletons hands as if he were riding a bicycle or closing his fists like he was going to punch someone? I rated it to stars because the help section of this isn't very helpful at all. And when I tried emailing the developers of this app the email would not go through, possibly an invalid email address
This app is amazing!!! Would be cool if you could draw muscle origins and insertions. Field of view zooming might be awesome, too. Range of motion constraints would be helpful, too.

Just got the Skelly app. Love all the features it has. If possible though, I would really love both a male and female skeleton to help learn the differences between the two, and an education mode that lists all the bones. Proko, if you're reading this, keep up the great work and thank you for all your awesome videos.
Love it but there really needs to be a "lock pose" button that locks the Angle, lighting and limbs. It's super sensitive which is great but can also be a hindrance.
Great item for students and vets and teachers

Awesome fabulous

If Skelly would have joint limitations, it would be best app ever) Also it would be great to have an option like  "Show Skelly with eyeballs". As for me, having a 3D reference of a skull with correct position of eyes would be just INCREDIBLY useful

Essential. Need it. Love it.

Great! Super useful! Wish I found this years ago!

Right now the only way to save multiple poses is to either make a new folder for each pose or override the one already saved.

I've tried a few posable figures on the Google Play store, this one is definitely my favourite! An option of adding multiple "Skellys" would be amazing!

Especially for a comic book artist looking to exaggerate an action pose. Besides those two things, love this app!

Great little app. If they manage to introduce flexible muscles at some point, it would be a killer app.
Takes a while to pick up, but great once you know how to work it.

One should be able to isolate primary objects. Only head or only ribcage or only pelvis aka bucket.  Right now it's very hard to rotate around any area. Maybe allow pivot focus, when item selected and controls are visible, you should be able to rotate around and not only rotate what is selected

Currently, I'm pretty happy with this app. The only thing that bothers me a lot is that Skelly doesn't have complete limitations to movement of any joint. For instance, hinge joint works properly, but you can rotate it the other way too. Leg or arm would have dislocation indeed. I believe guys can improve that in the foreseeable future. Keep up the good work

So I really love drawing, and I do a lot of studying from books like Micheal Hamtpons book.   The skelly thing lets me double check the poses I draw, helps me when I'm stuck but also doesn't give me everything. it doesn't have skin, or muscle. It gives you the anchors in a body, with the correct moving, and you have to use your brain to apply the information.  It genuinely is really useful. <3
Totally worth the money, probably the best art help app I've seen. Also the skeleton looks hilarious when you overstretch it's limits

Needs an undo button. Needs support for S-pen. All things considered this is a cool app that some people may find useful. I did find that getting a pose just right is rather difficult, especially when it is very easy for the app to misinterpret what part of the skelly you are trying to select, or what axis you are trying move the figure on. an undo button would allow you to quickly undo the mistake, but I spent more time fixing mistakes than on the actual pose. B-

This app is perfect for the studying artist and designer who want to learn how the skeleton looks from different angles and perspective. The inclusion of a simplified robo version is a great help as it simplifies the task of imagining poses and perspective; speeding up pose creation as well as a helpful intermediary step in drawing a realistic skeleton  +SUGGESTIONS: Muscles that stretch and bulge according to the pose. Source and insertion landmarks for those muscles. An addition of an even more simplified full body robo version that use cylinders and/or boxes with landmarks. This simplified version will help artist learn the simple shapes of the whole body and how the major parts relate to each other proportionally. -BUGS: Ribs get badly distorted when the spine is twisted.
The app is great but for the expense I would like more features, such as more than on figure per pose. It's a great app I just wish I got more with it.

downloading is tricky

One thing I'd love to see is a "reset view" button that centers the figure and gives you a front view to easily reset when you've been twisting and flying around all over the place. Incredible resource. Buy this app!

This is, I am excited to see now, not the case; not only has there been an update, it's a content update (as opposed to bug fixes/performance improvements). love it, exactly what the title says. If you're into Art GET IT!!

I would love to see a pose-saver function to help save time. Screen shots are an okay solution but it's nice to have all your things in one place.

Very useful!
this a great app. Needs a grid.

I give it a 3 stars for now. Amazing app but please fix the camera options. Zooming is too glitchy and fast. The panning isnt working; ive read someone else has the same issue. Like everyone else wants, a SAVE option. An undo button would be nice too. Please continue development. I've refunded it for now until it is fixed. Thank you.

I like the concept, to have a posable model, but this one is a little too simplified to help with my own need as a student.  I would like the joints to be limitted to normal human range. or at least turn the control red when outside normal range. full control of fingers and toes. And finally to choose a lens for the camera. obviously adding muscles and skin would be awesome too
I expected this to have joint limitations that mimicked the human body.
This is a very handy little app and very well designed.

I like the app! It's minimal, in a good way. very easy to just pick up and use.  my suggestions for updates would be  1. Add an "undo move" button   2. Add a "lock this joint" button-  So when I have a placement perfect, i don't accidentally mess with it later while moving another joint around.  3. Save poses!- "But you can just take a screenshot!" Not the same! If you add a "save pose" button, you could be able to reopen it later and alter it. This would help say, people who are trying to capture subtle movement, or if you felt like your pose didnt look realistic and wanted to try to go back n fix it!  4. Be able to change the color of the lighting!   These 4 suggestions i feel would be really easy to implement & would keep with the minimalist, easy-to use theme you guys got going.  (if you wanted to get real crazy, id say #5 add the option of placing lights, but id understand why you'd opt- out.)  Bottom line its a great app easy to use, i just wish it had alil more features.
Save a pose would be great for further editing...Otherwise amazing app.Love Proko's video tutorials as well.Purchased Figure drawing and worth every penny!Highly recommended.
The best app for artists and animators alike
Would love a "muscle" option and a "save" option.
No other way to close except FORCE EXIT. Save option PLEASE. When to expect Masses and Muscles?
I like it so far but an option to save a screen shot or make a jpg out of your pose would be helpful to transfer on to computer screen while working digitally.

The app is good, the skeleton (Skelly) is accurate, posing is nice; but the camera controlls aren't working too well on my device: camera rotation is good, but zooming is too fast, and the panning doesn't work. I'm using the Samsung Galaxy Tab 2 10.1.
I like that it has simplified forms as well as skeleton

As someone said, these apps usually have serious flaws and shortcomings that make them virtually unusable. This one doesn't. It's snappy, precise with great customization and really awesome future potential.  Regarding the performance that some users seem to complain about - i'm not sure if it's hardware or iOS, but i'm using this app on a fairly weak Nexus 7, 2,5 years old and it runs just perfectly.  Now to the improvement possibilities.  * Stan should consider releasing this for windows/desktop computers. Tablets are awesome, but i do most of my work with my computer within reach and i want my stuff on my screens, not a tablet. * We need an easy way to make and send/upload screenshots from the app. Currently i'm solving this by using the app "Easyscreenshot" and then uploading the pictures to Dropbox, where i can display them on my computer screen. It works quite well, but for some users this may be an annoying walk-around.  All in all, awesome work on this app, Stan - keep it up and update it as you see fit!

good app for reference of skeleton and basic movement. maybe add some kind of libary of preloaded and ability to saved poses would save time setting up.                                                                  (As a paided app future feature update wish list - swap between female and male skeleton option and basic  muscle layout )

I spent 8 eur for an extremely slow app. 1-It Would have been great to see the names of every bone selected. 2- The zoom is inconvenient, is not fluid. To have the image size desired, I have to take several minutes to zoom. - There isn't "up and down" to scroll the zoomed image. 3- There isn't forearm supination and pronation, and it was important. It was important to see how the forearm rotates, but this does not happen. 4-Not worth the money spent. Too bad because i'm searching for an app like this for years, since i am a comic artist.
absolutely unworkable app, please erase it anywhere, anytime

Wonderful tool, easy interface. Was toiling around with it and couldn't find and option for fingers or toes. The models could use colors too or options. Maybe proko could implement his style of art wrapped around as and added incentive I.e robo bean, bowl hips, etc. A little more can be worked around and I have found useful 3d models on the internet for free, on mobile even, but this is convenient too. More can be done for $6.99

Great to and manipulate the model, but should the joints be locked so they can't move into odd positions. After all we can't move our heads into our rib cage normally. Also some pre set poses would help

This looks amazing! It's definitely useful. I love how easy it is to change the pose. Unlike a lot of 3D reference apps I've tried, the zoom and rotation of the camera are very intuitive. The skeleton itself looks very detailed and accurate. All that said, it could be a lot better. I would like the ability to save poses, export image files, open/close the hands, and add an additional light or two. I would also like more control over the brightness of the light and what kind of light (i.e. point light, sun light, etc)
Would be nice if it had some canned pose presets.

Normally these types of apps fall short in performance and detail. I'm actually quite impressed with everything I've seen so far; very high quality! Just need a 'save pose for later' option, rather than having to rely on screenshots.

Every thing works exactly as you would expect it to, amazingly easy to adopt and perfectly intuitive. Not to mention the perfect extension from the Proko YouTube channels. I'd hate to add to the list of please add this and that, but I would just be gravy if you could add constructions lines to the Lumos model. it would be great if I could see how the hair line, nose line, mouth line etc. These are my greatest short coming in anatomy and would make the app spotless for me. thank you for the wonderful app.
Is so goddamned wonderful I could cry :'D! Exactly what I've been looking for and waiting for... The interface runs smoothly and is incredibly easy to use. Couldn't ask for a better app!

As an illustrator who has been wanting this exact kind of app I immediately shelled out the cash when I saw it posted. I love the easy interface and everything about the app is wonderful and simple BUT the inability to save a pose or export it into an image file makes this far less practical for me. I'm using this on a large phone but it's still difficult to draw from such a small reference and it's a real battery drain keeping my phone on to maintain one pose.
Already awesome, but if the jaw moved, it would be cooler. I have trouble drawing a screaming skull character.
Love your  videos keep it up!!!

Guru Proko is my all time favorite on Youtube :D This is great and must must must have application for the artists, who are into human anatomy. Easy intuitive interface.  I wish that Muscle anatomy, along with pose save option may be added on to this, so that it can become one of the top reference applications in the World! I am so happy that I purchased this app - works excellent on my Google Nexus 6. Thanks a ton, Stan!
Great Stuff. Will be very useful when I need references. Thanks!
Really slick - as someone else said in their review incredibly intuitive and lots of fun - love it. Would be useful if you could save poses.

Love this app, it has every thing you need to practice drawing the Anatomy, the fact it has all the other stuff like lighting, zooming, rotation making the anatomy look solid too. Gonna have have fun using this app. 👏👍
I've waited a long time for this!

Amazing ! Been waiting for app like this for years ! Hopefully it will someday include possibility to save your favourite poses, to add muscles and maybe mini skelly (for drawing kids) or even better an option to adjust size of individual parts of the body and height. Surely there is a LOT of promise here. Even in its current stage its still best thing ever - don't hesitate, buy it ! You wont regret it !

Oh man, I love it! Posing, navigation,  and lighting is super intuitive! I suggest Android users avoid relaunching the app via shortcut, as you will lose your pose. It will revert to default pose. Keep it open. Proko underscores why his brand works so well for the education of artists... So much time and effort,  quality and cleverness goes into each thing he releases. This app is just incredible! The definition of pro. Monstrous kudos!!
Great app. For someone who struggles with light source, I'm happy that this app allows me to place the light source where I please. Only with it would allow for fingers to be pose-able as well.
